    "nh_founder_rt9aXm": {
      "type": "nh-founder",
      "blocks": {
        "text_T4Npjw": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "column": "left",
            "row": 1,
            "content": "<p>Hi, my names Sabbah.</p>",
            "font_size_desktop": 20,
            "font_size_mobile": 0,
            "hide_mobile": false,
            "hide_desktop": false
          }
        },
        "text_JhkQAM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "column": "right",
            "row": 2,
            "content": "<p>For generations, women were nourished with whole, nutrient-dense foods that supported energy, resilience, and vitality at the root. Organs like liver and spleen weren’t trends — they were foundational nutrition. The problem was, I couldn’t bring myself to eat liver or organ meats consistently!</p>",
            "font_size_desktop": 0,
            "font_size_mobile": 0,
            "hide_mobile": true,
            "hide_desktop": false
          }
        },
        "image_tdnb4Q": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "column": "left",
            "row": 1,
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/CRV-new-zealand-grazing_feature-image.jpg",
            "image_url": "",
            "hide_mobile": false,
            "hide_desktop": true
          }
        },
        "text_7Tzpcw": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "column": "left",
            "row": 1,
            "content": "<p>As a doctor working long, demanding shifts, I lived in a constant state of exhaustion. My energy was low, my focus was slipping, and no matter how much I slept, I never felt restored. Iron tablets upset my stomach, and multivitamins felt synthetic and disconnected from real nourishment. </p><p>That’s when I began a deep dive into <strong>wholefood nutrition</strong>.</p>",
            "font_size_desktop": 20,
            "font_size_mobile": 0,
            "hide_mobile": false,
            "hide_desktop": false
          }
        },
        "text_pjkrJr": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "column": "right",
            "row": 2,
            "content": "<p>I knew there was no organ supplement on the market designed around what women actually need — our hormonal demands, our iron losses, our biology. That’s when I decided to create <strong>Nourish Her</strong>™. To make it easier to get the essential nutrients my body needed.</p><p>For the first time in a long while, it felt like my body was finally getting what it had been asking for.</p>",
            "font_size_desktop": 0,
            "font_size_mobile": 0,
            "hide_mobile": false,
            "hide_desktop": false
          }
        },
        "text_FiGndy": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "column": "left",
            "row": 1,
            "content": "<p>For generations, women were nourished with whole, nutrient-dense foods that supported energy, resilience, and vitality at the root. Organs like liver and spleen weren’t trends — they were foundational nutrition. The problem was, I couldn’t bring myself to eat liver or organ meats consistently!</p>",
            "font_size_desktop": 0,
            "font_size_mobile": 0,
            "hide_mobile": false,
            "hide_desktop": true
          }
        },
        "image_RPPQyt": {
          "type": "image",
